import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['num_dependencies'], bins=24, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['num_dependencies'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of dependencies?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['source'], data['target'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between source and target?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    source_count = data['source'].value_counts()
    source_count.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common source?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=source_count.max(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend([f'Most common source: {source_count.idxmax()} ({source_count.max():.2f})'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    target_counts = data['target'].value_counts()
    target_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common target?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=target_counts.max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Max value: {target_counts.max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data.groupby('source')['num_dependencies'].apply(list), showfliers=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Dependencies')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of the number of dependencies for each source?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
